'''S'''imple '''D'''esktop '''D'''isplay '''M'''anager (SDDM) is a [[display manager]] supports X11 and Wayland. 

== Installation ==

=== USE flags ===

{{USEflag|package=x11-misc/sddm|desc=Optional USE flags for {{Package|x11-misc/sddm}}:
|consolekit+++ Use ck-launch-session from sys-auth/consolekit by default in Xsession (no native support)
|systemd
|upower
}}

=== Emerge ===

Install {{Package|x11-misc/sddm}}:

{{Emerge|x11-misc/sddm}}

== Configuration ==

The configuration file for SDDM is: {{Path|/etc/sddm.conf}}

=== Boot service ===

To start SDDM on boot:

{{RootCmd|systemctl enable sddm.service}}

To start SDDM now:

{{RootCmd|systemctl start sddm.service}}

